      In the high valleys of **Veythar**, where the wind carried the voices of the dead, there stood a lone waystation tended by **Mira the Silent**. Her only rule was this: *‘No guest may leave without breaking bread—or the bowl shall break them.’* The bowl was ancient, its rim etched with the names of those who had eaten from it, and it was said that to refuse its offering was to invite the **Hunger of the Unfed**, a spirit that gnawed at the bones of the ungrateful.

