      In the desert city of **Korvann**, where the sun bleached the bones of the unwise, there stood the **House of the Thirsty**—a caravanserai where no traveler was denied water. The rule was absolute: *‘Drink, and the cup will remember you. Refuse, and the desert will claim your name.’* The cup was a relic of **Sylas the Parched**, a god who had once begged for water and been denied, and now his thirst lived in the clay.

