      In the frozen village of **Veythar’s Maw**, where the wind carried the voices of the dead, there stood a single hearth tended by **Old Haldor**. The rule was carved into the mantel: *‘No traveler may leave without warming their hands at the fire. To deny the flame is to invite the Cold That Eats Souls.’* The hearth was sacred, its embers said to hold the last breath of **Veythar the Frozen**, a god who had once begged for warmth and been cast into the blizzard.

